    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and rotary performance. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, delivering a linear power band with seamless transition between primary and secondary boost phases. The chassis is anchored by a sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the 50/50 weight distribution is fully exploited. Every vacuum line, bushing, and apex seal has been meticulously maintained to factory specifications. With original paint and a pristine cockpit, this is a turn-key investment for the enthusiast who demands mechanical perfection and uncompromised JDM heritage.",
      "price": 48500.0,
